Document: Convexpolygonshape2d  
Path: godot/classes/class_convexpolygonshape2d.rst  
Summary: A 2D convex polygon shape for physics, used internally in CollisionPolygon2D when in BUILD_SOLIDS mode.  

ConvexPolygonShape2D is solid, detecting collisions from objects fully inside it, unlike ConcavePolygonShape2D which is hollow. This makes it more suitable for both detection and physics. Convex decomposition splits concave polygons into convex ones, enabling complex collision shapes via multiple ConvexPolygonShape2D nodes or CollisionPolygon2D in BUILD_SOLIDS mode. To generate a collision polygon from a Sprite2D, select the node, open the Sprite2D menu above the viewport, and choose "Create Polygon2D Sibling." ConvexPolygonShape2D is faster than ConcavePolygonShape2D but slower than primitive shapes like CircleShape2D and RectangleShape2D. It should be used for medium-sized objects when primitive shapes cannot accurately represent the collision.
---CHUNK---
