Document: ConvexPolygonShape2D
Path: godot/classes/class_convexpolygonshape2d.rst
Summary: Defines the points property for ConvexPolygonShape2D and its constraints for forming a convex hull.

Property: points (PackedVector2Array): The polygon's list of vertices that form a convex hull. Can be in either clockwise or counterclockwise order. Default: PackedVector2Array()

Method: set_points(value: PackedVector2Array) → void
Method: get_points() → PackedVector2Array

Warning: Only set this property to a list of points that actually form a convex hull. Use set_point_cloud() to generate the convex hull of an arbitrary set of points.
Note: The returned array is copied and any changes to it will not update the original property value. See PackedVector2Array for more details.
---CHUNK---
Document: ConvexPolygonShape2D
Path: godot/classes/class_convexpolygonshape2d.rst
Summary: The set_point_cloud method assigns points using a convex hull algorithm, removing redundant points.

Method: set_point_cloud(point_cloud: PackedVector2Array) → void
Based on the set of points provided, this assigns the points property using the convex hull algorithm, removing all unneeded points. See Geometry2D.convex_hull() for details.